      <prefercite id="aspace_f3cd593b4cb859bb7cf390704ad62796">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Collection of Bookplates by Hans Ranzoni the Younger, Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library, Yale University.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_7d7797a74dc92b9f1752d25806e3245a">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Hans Ranzoni the Younger (1896-1991) was an Austrian graphic artist and engraver, active in Vienna. In addition to designing bookplates, he created other illustrations as well as stamp designs.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_e36ec41d569cdd3778db570c944a3343">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection contains bookplates by Hans Ranzoni the Younger, an Austrian graphic artist and engraver. In addition to ex-libris, the collection also contains greeting cards, business cards, and postage stamps designed by Ranzoni.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_db6bd8cc88c482a7e9595589963a1682">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into three series: I. Bookplates – Individuals. II. Bookplates – Duplicates. III. Other Works.</p>  
      </arrangement>
